      <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p>At PICASF Consulting, we are committed to protecting and respecting your privacy. This Cookie Policy explains how we use cookies on our website and how you can manage your cookie preferences.</p>
      
      <h2>What Are Cookies?</h2>
      <p>Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work or work more efficiently, as well as to provide information to the site owners.</p>

      <h2>How We Use Cookies</h2>
      <p>We use cookies to enhance your browsing experience by:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Remembering your preferences and settings for future visits.</li>
        <li>Providing social media features and analyzing web traffic.</li>
        <li>Personalizing content based on your interests.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
      <p>We use the following types of cookies on our website:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Strictly Necessary Cookies</strong>: These cookies are essential for the operation of our website and cannot be disabled in our systems. They are typically set in response to actions made by you, such as logging in or filling out forms.</li>
        <li><strong>Performance Cookies</strong>: These cookies allow us to measure and analyze the performance of our website, helping us improve its functionality. They collect information on how visitors use the site, such as which pages are visited most often.</li>
        <li><strong>Functionality Cookies</strong>: These cookies help our website remember choices you make (such as language preferences) to provide a more personalized experience.</li>
        <li><strong>Targeting Cookies</strong>: These cookies are used to deliver targeted advertising and track the effectiveness of our marketing campaigns.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Managing Your Cookie Preferences</h2>
      <p>You can manage your cookie preferences by adjusting the settings on your browser. Most browsers allow you to block cookies or alert you when a cookie is being sent. However, if you disable cookies, you may not be able to use some features of our website.</p>
      <p>For more information on how to manage cookies, please visit your browser’s help section or the following pages:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.allaboutcookies.org/manage-cookies/" target="_blank">All About Cookies - Managing Cookies</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.aboutcookies.org/" target="_blank">About Cookies</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Third-Party Cookies</h2>
      <p>We may also allow third-party service providers to set cookies on our website for the purposes of providing analytics, advertising, and social media features. These third parties are subject to their own cookie policies.</p>

      <h2>Changes to This Cookie Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update our Cookie Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the “Last Updated” date at the bottom of this page will be revised accordingly. Please check this page periodically to stay informed about how we are using cookies.</p>

